description:
&lt;p&gt;Band 5 Staff Nurse – Rheumatology &amp; Lupus Infusion suite and Outpatients department&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for a dedicated and experienced Band 5 nurse to join our passionate, committed and innovative team that deliver excellent standards of care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Rheumatology and Lupus unit is part of the Directorate of Specialist Ambulatory Service (SAS) and it is a EULAR Centre of Excellence in Rheumatology. In addition, it has a BSR Emerging Best Practice Award 2016 for Fibromyalgia Clinic, CSR Outstanding Best Practice Awards 2013 for RA Centre, GRAPPA International Centre of Excellence for Psoriatic Arthritis Care and Lupus UK Centre of Excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be part of a team of nurses who are responsible for the smooth running of the infusion suite and support the patient journey through the rheumatology and lupus outpatient department. The infusion suite is open Monday to Friday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants without Rheumatology and Lupus experience are welcomed to apply and will be given the right support to excel in the role. The successful candidate will be offered training and developmental opportunities within a motivated and enthusiastic team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Advert closing: 22nd November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date: 3rd December 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Laura Blackler, Advanced Nurse Practitioner, laura.blackler@gstt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Akaribire Zakari, Charge Nurse - Akaribire.Zakari@gstt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
